<br>
For Llily:<br>
<br>
1. Count the number of vowels in the name <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Two.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
2. Deduct the number of consonants<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>-Three = -One (off to a good start!)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
3. For each double vowel ie &quot;aa&quot; &quot;ee&quot; - Add 5<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Hurray for double constants!  Still -One.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
4. If name is exactly 6 letters long - Minus 1<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Still -One.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
5. If name is exactly 5 letters long - Minus 2<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>That's me!  -One - Two = -Three!</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
6. If name is exactly 4 letters long - Minus 4<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>-Three.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
7. If name is greater than 10 letters long - Add 4<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Nope!  -Three.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
8. If name is a pun or play on words - Add 5<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Nope!  -Three.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
9. If name ends with a vowel - Add 2<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Aww - this one is just silly.  Lots of practical names end in vowels!  Regardless, -Three + Two = -One.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
10. If name begins with a vowel - Add 2<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Phew.  -One.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
11. If name consists entirely of alternating Consonants and Vowels - Minus 4<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Close but no cigar.  -One.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
12. If name contains name of animal, type of weather, plant, domestic appliance or type of furniture - Add 5<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Sucks if your name is Maytagrefridgerator.  Also sucks if your name happens to be a type of flower.  -One + Five = +Four.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Llily gets a +4.<br>
<br>
